[{"id":42426,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>6</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>12</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Given:&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></math></p><p>Using relation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>&#969;</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></math></p><p>Integrating the above,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>&#969;</mi></msubsup><mo>d</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Now,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>&#952;</mi></msubsup><mo>d</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mo>&#8747;</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>t</mi></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mn>10</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></math></p><p>Integrating the above relation,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p><p>Thus, angular position of the ball is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42439,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/dbf91892-3d45-4b1b-9372-466b5cbe2bfc-image.png\" style=\"width: 206px; height: 216px;\" /></p><p>Both velocity vectors are of same magnitude therefore resultant would pass exactly midway through them&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42377,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["\\(\\frac{1-\\tan \\alpha}{1+\\tan \\alpha}\\)","\\(\\frac{1-\\sin 2 \\alpha}{1+\\sin 2 \\alpha}\\)","\\(\\frac{1+\\sin 2 \\alpha}{1-\\sin 2 \\alpha}\\)","\\(\\frac{1+\\sin \\alpha}{1-\\sin \\alpha}\\)"],"answer":1,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{H}_{\\mathrm{Max}}=\\frac{(\\mathrm{u} \\sin \\theta)^2}{2 \\mathrm{~g}} \\\\ & \\frac{\\left(\\mathrm{H}_{\\max }\\right)_1}{\\left(\\mathrm{H}_{\\max }\\right)_2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{u}^2 \\sin ^2(45-\\alpha)}{\\mathrm{u}^2 \\sin ^2(45+\\alpha)} \\\\ & =\\frac{\\left(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\cos \\alpha-\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\sin \\alpha\\right)^2}{\\left(\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\cos \\alpha+\\frac{1}{\\sqrt{2}} \\sin \\alpha\\right)^2} \\\\ & =\\frac{1-\\sin 2 \\alpha}{1+\\sin 2 \\alpha}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42421,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>:</mo><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Let projection speed is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math>, The formula for the range of the projectile is given by,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math>. Therefore,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>90</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>90</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42369,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["$1: 4$","$2: 3$","$3: 4$","$1: 2$"],"answer":2,"solution":"At A: $KE_A = K$, $v_A = v$, angle $= 60°$.<br>At B (highest point): $v_B = v\\cos 60° = v/2$, so $KE_B = K/4$.<br>At C (same level as A): by energy conservation, $KE_C = K$.<br>$|KE_B - KE_C| = |K/4 - K| = 3K/4$.<br>Ratio $= \\frac{3K/4}{K} = \\frac{3}{4}$, i.e., $3:4$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42412,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>4</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>3</mn></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Let stone is projected with initial velocity&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e7309dd1-ed39-4229-a7af-2312617a05c4-9894893.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 87px;\" /></p><p>Kinetic energy&nbsp;of the stone at point of projection is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p><p>Now, velocity of stone at maximum height is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>cos</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>, so kinetic energy at that point is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>v</mi><mi>cos</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Hence, the ratio&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><mrow><mi>K</mi><msub><mi>E</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>v</mi><mi>cos</mi><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mstyle></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42482,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{K}$","Zero","$\\mathrm{K} / 2$","$\\mathrm{K} / 4$"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":42477,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>25</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math> <mrow> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mtext>v</mtext> <mo>&rarr;</mo> </mover> <mo>=</mo> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mtext>i</mtext> <mo>^</mo> </mover> <mo>+</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mover accent=\"true\"> <mtext>j</mtext> <mo>^</mo> </mover> </mrow> </math><br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mo>&rArr;</mo> <mtext>x</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mtext>t</mtext> </mrow> </math>&nbsp;&nbsp; ..... (i)<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mtext>y</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>t</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </mfrac> <mfenced close=\")\" open=\"(\" separators=\",\"> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mn>0</mn> <msup> <mtext>t</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mfenced> </mrow> </math>&nbsp;&nbsp; ..... (ii)<br /><br />From (i) and (ii)<br /><br /><math> <mrow> <mtext>y</mtext> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mtext>x</mtext> <mo>-</mo> <mn>5</mn> <msup> <mtext>x</mtext> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (07 Apr)","image":null},{"id":42368,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["15","20","25","10"],"answer":0,"solution":"For projectile motion at 45°, vertical component of initial velocity:<br>$v_{0y} = v_0 \\sin 45° = \\frac{v_0}{\\sqrt{2}}$<br>Maximum height occurs at $t = 2$ s when $v_y = 0$:<br>$0 = v_{0y} - gt$<br>$\\Rightarrow v_{0y} = 10 \\times 2 = 20$ m/s<br>Thus $\\frac{v_0}{\\sqrt{2}} = 20$, so $v_0 = 20\\sqrt{2}$ m/s<br>Height at landing time $t = 3$ s:<br>$H = v_{0y}t - \\frac{1}{2}gt^2 = 20 \\times 3 - \\frac{1}{2} \\times 10 \\times 9$<br>$= 60 - 45 = 15$ m","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (24 January Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42462,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>/</mo><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"We know for complementary angle range is same for same projection speed.<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#952;</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> &hellip;.. (i)<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#952;</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> &hellip;.. (ii)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi>n&#952;c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#952;</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mfrac></math> .&hellip; (iii)<br />From equation (i) and (ii)<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">U</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#952;</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#952;</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br />(Using the value of R from equation iii)<br /><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42428,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>25</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>30</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4137abf6-25b5-4291-ac44-7a9ad379200a-image.png\" style=\"width: 146px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>r</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>g</mi></msub></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9d48137a-0230-46ec-a8d6-1a19720e0957-image.png\" style=\"width: 225px; height: 180px;\" />&nbsp;</p><p>From the above diagram, velocity of the raindrop wrt ground will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>r</mi></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msqrt><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>15</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>15</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p>And velocity of the raindrop wrt the moving girl will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"|\" open=\"|\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>v</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mrow><mi>r</mi><mi>g</mi></mrow></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>30</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>km</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42466,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mfenced separators=\\\"|\\\"><mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mover accent=\\\"true\\\"><mi mathvariant=\\\"normal\\\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mfenced separators=\\\"|\\\"><mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mover accent=\\\"true\\\"><mi mathvariant=\\\"normal\\\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mfenced separators=\\\"|\\\"><mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mover accent=\\\"true\\\"><mi mathvariant=\\\"normal\\\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mfenced separators=\\\"|\\\"><mrow><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>R</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mover accent=\\\"true\\\"><mi mathvariant=\\\"normal\\\">i</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p><math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#960;</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>&#969;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/da5b0094-c9e2-4218-81d6-c5782332db7a-image.png\" style=\"width: 292px; height: 250px;\" /></p><p><math><msub><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><msub><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>-</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mi>&#969;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced><mover accent=\"true\"><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42423,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Given here, initial velocity,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>x</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p><p>Equation of trajectory,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p>Now, differentiating the above equation,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>For initial <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-component of velocity</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>5</mn><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>u</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo></mover><mi>y</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mover><mi>j</mi><mo>^</mo></mover></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42440,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c4dbf841-1106-47a3-8739-1cd2c2c32800-image.png\" style=\"width: 407px; height: 173px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"italic\">R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>Energy conservation</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>{</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>}</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p><p>&nbsp;from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mfenced close=\"}\" open=\"{\"><mfrac><mi>h</mi><mi>R</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>g</mi><mo>{</mo><mi>R</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>}</mo></mrow><mi>R</mi></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42406,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>u</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0f9f62ca-2f9d-4a2f-a957-720ecd338fef-9888679.PNG\" style=\"width: 310px; height: 134px;\" /></p><p>At maximum height, only horizontal velocity of the particle remains. Let the angle of project be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi></math>. The horizontal velocity of the particle will remain same, therefore</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mi>u</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math></p><p>Now, time of flight of projectile is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>u</mi><mi>sin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>u</mi><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42444,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1ecf8d3a-8c26-4f44-904c-852c9ad4f66d-image.png\" style=\"width: 325px; height: 254px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>k</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>K</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>m</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><msqrt><mfrac><mn>100</mn><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>10</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt></math><br />From <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>g</mi><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>h</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>g</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>v</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt><mo>&#215;</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>10</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42402,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is false but&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is true","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;is true but&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is false","<p>Both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> are correct and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is the correct explanation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math></p>","<p>Both <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> are correct but <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is NOT the correct explanation of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Horizontal range of a projectile from a horizontal plane is given by,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>u</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math>.</p><p>Clearly for maximum range,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p><p>Therefore,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>45</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></math>.</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42460,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"We get same range for angle of projections <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mn>90</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></math> . <br/><math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>  <br/><math><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>  <br/><math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math>  <br/><math><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">θ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>  <br/><math><mo>∴</mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":42485,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["$\\frac{u}{3}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{u}}{2}$","$\\frac{2 u}{3}$","$\\frac{\\mathrm{u}}{\\sqrt{3}}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/SYCRfCuL70-VRRHRH7OKc0mqwZnfHC7Jgj0Tu1VCKK0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n$\\mathrm{u} \\cos 60^{\\circ}=\\mathrm{v} \\cos 30^{\\circ}$\n$$\nv=\\frac{4}{\\sqrt{3}}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2005","image":null},{"id":42455,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>C</mi></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>C</mi></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi></msqrt><mi>C</mi></mfrac></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f4f3c6ed-acf0-4b8b-bb86-fadd3660dc0a-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 179px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><msup><mi>&#969;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>acos</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>mgsin</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>g</mi><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>c</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>x</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>tan</mi><mi>&#952;</mi><msub><mo>)</mo><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#969;</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>ac</mi></mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>2</mn><mi>g</mi><mi>C</mi></msqrt></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (02 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42393,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><msqrt><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msqrt><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></msqrt></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4390de5e-c919-42bc-a03c-cff4b8edc61e.png\" style=\"width: 380px; height: 217px;\" /></p><p>The displacement is the hypotenuse of the diameter and the distance travelled for half the rotation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>R</mi></math>.</p><p>By using Pythagoras theorem,</p><p>Displacement of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>R</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>&#960;</mi><mi>R</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi>R</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>&#960;</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></msqrt></math></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (13 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":42385,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Motion In Two Dimensions","question":"","options":["uniformly accelerated having motion along a parabolic path.","uniform motion along a straight line.","uniformly accelerated having motion along a straight line.","non-uniformly accelerated."],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned}\n& x=2+4 t \\\\\n& \\frac{d x}{d t}=v_x=4 \\\\\n& \\frac{d v_x}{d t}=a_x=0 \\\\\n& y=3 t+8 t^2 \\\\\n& \\frac{d y}{d t}=v_y=3+16 t \\\\\n& \\frac{d v_y}{d t}=a_y=16\n\\end{aligned}$\nthe motion will be uniformly accelerated motion.\nFor path\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\mathrm{x}=2+4 \\mathrm{t} \\\\\n& \\frac{(\\mathrm{x}-2)}{4}=\\mathrm{t}\n\\end{aligned}$<br />Put this value of $t$ is equation of $y$\n$y=3\\left(\\frac{x-2}{4}\\right)+8\\left(\\frac{x-2}{4}\\right)^2$\nthis is a quadratic equation so path will be parabola.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (04 Apr Shift 1)","image":null}]